    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-10-24T18:28:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-10-24T18:28:00-05:00" n="154"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <head>154. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission to the United
                        Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d154fn1">Source: National Archives, RG 59,
                        Central Files 1967–69, <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> 10–4.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-10-24T23:28:00+00:00">October 24, 1969,
                        2328Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3774. Subject: <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Scale of Assessments.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_YCW1">Yost</persName> has informed Perm Reps of
                        Brazil, Mexico and Peru of US position this matter with fol results.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Brazil noncommital but said would look into matter.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Mexico and Peru said would not cosponsor <gloss target="#t_RES1"
                            >res</gloss> providing additional maximum reduction for low per capita
                        income countries but would probably vote for it if tabled.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Faura (Peru) informed <persName corresp="#p_DDS1">Da Mota</persName>
                        (Brazil) of Peruvian decision not cosponsor and found <persName
                            corresp="#p_DDS1">Da Mota</persName> quite depressed at present
                        situation. Faura said he did not believe Peru would have vote for <gloss
                            target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> if tabled.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SA1">Shahi</persName> (Pakistan) informed <gloss
                            target="#t_MISOFF1">MISOFF</gloss> his <gloss target="#t_DEL1"
                            >del</gloss> would not cosponsor and he would endeavor convince
                            <persName corresp="#p_DDS1">Da Mota</persName> not table res.</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>Sadry (Iran) said Vakil seeking instructions and had suggested to FonOff
                        Iranian <persName corresp="#p_DCM1">Del</persName> vote for <gloss
                            target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> if tabled since it would save Iran money.
                        Sadry felt certain Iran would not cosponsor.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_YCW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Yost</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
